{
  "text": "A na\u00efve approach for implementing an interleaver is to use lookup tables (LUT) to store all of the possible interleaving patterns in a memory. The excessive memory requirement of Write back means the data is written back to the same address from which it is read (b) Proposed scheduling for high-throughput parallel decoding [CITATION_1] . Numbers in parentheses show scheduling steps.",
